728. Perduis. The Latin ‘Subjunctive' forms in -ίφη, sim (older siem), velim, edim, 816. are relies of the Optative Mood. Thus eelim, ereduim (from cluo, a by-form both of do, ‘to give,' and -do, ‘to put') were origin- ally Optatives, while edam, credebam were Subjunctives. In Plautus the distinction is already to a great extent lost. Duim, per-duim are however found mainly in prayers and execrations, thus retaining their Optative character.
